The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Raphael, Pat to play with Jeev

Akron (US): Indias Jeev Milkha Singh has been grouped with Frances Raphael Jacquelin and American Pat Perez for the first two rounds of next weeks PGA Championship in Tulsa, Oklahoma. 

Title-holder Tiger Woods will play with fellow-Americans and former winners Rich Beem (2002) and Bob Tway (1986) at the last of the years four majors that begins next Thursday. 

World No.1 Woods, who will be bidding for his 13th major title, cruised to victory by five strokes in last years PGA Championship held in Medinah. 

Phil Mickelson, the 2005 winner in Baltusrol, has been paired with fellow-Americans David Toms and Jeff Sluman at the Southern Hills Country Club. 

In other high-profile grouping, world No. 2 Jim Furyk has been drawn with Britains Luke Donald and Jonathan Byrd of the US, while Ernie Els will play with eight-time European No. 1 Colin Montgomerie and American Stewart Cink. 

